						               													<description>Combat Team Command is a set of miniature wargame rules that allow players to take on the role of a battlegroup commander in charge of a combined arms force using small scale miniatures such as 1/300, 1/285, 10mm or 15mm.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules provided in this book deal primarily with the cold war period, notably a hypothetical third world war during the 1980s. The rules can be used to fight earlier or later conflicts. Army lists for the following conflicts are included&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     1980s Cold War Gone Hot&amp;#10;     Arab Israeli Wars&amp;#10;     1991 Gulf War&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The key focus of these rules is on the effective command and control or a player&amp;rsquo;s force. It is vital for players to correctly assign orders to the formations and units under the command of their officers to keep them fighting effectively.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The rules also use a card driven activation system that successfully creates a &amp;quot;fog of war&amp;quot; and keeps both players busy all the time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
